                <br />
                <br />
                <hr style="color:#e2e2e2;"/>
                <br />
Xml bound answertypes are bound to an Xml file available on the server.<br />
<br />
An Xml bound answertype will read the Xml file to which they are bound and show
the choices inside a dropdown list. It is very easy to create and bind
new Xml bound answertypes to custom Xml files using the online Answer%20Type%20Creator.html.<br />
<br />
The following default xml bound types are available :<br />
<br />
* Xml%20-%20Country.html<br />
* Xml%20-%20US%20States.html<br />
<br />
Xml files are based on the current language settings. Survey Project will 
                read Xml files based on the language Survey Project is running in, before reading
the default XML file. eg: If an Xml type is bound to a file called
&quot;country.xml&quot; this will be the default file, if switching to French for
example another Xml file called &quot;country.fr.xml&quot; is needed that will
be automatically read in when the survey is in French. This way it is
very easy to provide a translated version of a single Xml bound type to
different audiences.<br />
